CatDescriptText: Mrs. Elizabeth Jackson, housewife, 3306 Iowa Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that we are spending too much money for foreign aid? Do you think that what we have spent has halted the spread of communism?" answer reads: "Truly I think that we are spending too much money for foreign aid.  We should try to clean up here, attempt to make living conditions a lot better for our people here."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elizabeth Jackson wearing a patterned top and light colored overcoat, standing on Liberty Avenue with Dimlings Candy and Baum Building in background, Downtown
